The frame has been modified with the innovative Ed Brown Bobtail housing which reduces the projecting butt of the mainspring housing without sacrificing the full size frame and magazine capacity. The Bobtail minimizes the print under your jacket when carrying and reduces weight. Officer's frames reduce magazine capacity and limit grip, while keeping the projecting, sharp butt. Slides shorter than 4.25" are notorious for reduced reliability. These problems are eliminated with the Ed Brown Commander Bobtail configuration, which reflects the genius of John Browning with an innovative modern flair. The functional simplicity has yet to be matched. Unique with the Kobra series pistols is the innovative snakeskin treatment. It is a directional pattern, meaning it is smooth to slide your hand up, but bites in for a snug grip the other way where you need it. It's easier on the hands than checkering, and our female customers in particular can't stop bragging about it. Not to mention it just looks cool! The Kobra Carry is an innovative masterpiece, and a serious tool for those who want something a little different. We are sure you'll be charmed by the Kobra Carry!

The OPAP's are much harder to find and much more desirable than the commonly found NPAP variant. This gun still appears as new finish wise. It does have Yugoslav military furniture. The handguards are M70, the buttstock is from an M76 sniper. The straight comb of the M76 stock eliminates the so called "cheak slap" that is common on the M70 and NPAP variants and positions your head properly on the sights. Not only that, it looks nicer (IMO). This rifle comes with one Yugo bolt hold open 30 round mag (I have many others listed seperately). It also comes with a cleaning rod, original Yugo sling, and 2 muzzle brakes - borth a slant brake and a birdcage brake (both Tapco). This gun is 922r compliant, as it was made for Century at the Zastava arsenal in Yugoslavia (with the exception of the M76 stock which was added). It is matching - except for the M76 buttstock of course.

The PAP M77PS is a semi-auto version of the Serbian military M77B1 AK DMR, which itself is a modernized version of the classic Zastava M76 DMR. The M77PS features an AK47 type operating system; scaled up to fire the larger 7.62x51mm cartridge. It has a 20" long Cold Hammer Fordged barrel, with 14mm threaded muzzle. The receiver accepts double stack magazines and is made from reinforced 1.5mm thick stamped steel. Other features include an adjustable gas system, adjustable front and rear sights, standard full-length side scope rail, bolt hold open notched safety, milspec polymer furniture with sling studs, rubber recoil pad, and a smooth and crisp double hook type trigger group. All of the internal parts are made from milled/forged steel, and are not cast or contain any polymer. All parts were made in Serbia at the Zastava Arms factory, and all are 100% new and not military surplus. This rifle does not require 922(r) parts, as like with the Romanian PSL, the ATF considers it to be a 'Sporting' rifle. Rifle comes complete with 2 - 10 round Zastava magazine made from steel. It will accept preban Mitchell type mags too. It also has a factory owner's manual and 1 year importer's warranty. As i said, it comes with polymer furniture, but it can accept wood sets intended for the M76, so you may customize it. This really is a very high quality rifle, especially for the money. It has been on the market for half a year now, and most every review agrees that it is well built, accurate, and above all; very reliable and durable. If you have any questions at all, please feel free to contact me anytime. Thanks so much for your time and interest.
